  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Couple escapes to Ramanadapuram hospital",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "An elderly couple who went to India illegally by sea from the Mannar coast were rescued by the Indian Coast Guard yesterday (28) when they fell asleep at Rameshwaram Dhanuskodi beach.",
        "The 74-year-old and the 67-year-old couple, who hail from the Marungan area in Mannar, had set sail for India from the Mannar coast on the 27th with the help of a fishing vessel.",
        "The elderly couple saw a fisherman lying unconscious on the Dhanushkodi beach and after informing the Coast Guard, the officers immediately rushed the couple to the Ramanadapuram Government Hospital in India.",
        "However, the condition of the elderly couple receiving treatment is reported to be somewhat serious and the Indian Coast Guard has taken steps to tighten security at sea borders to stop the unsafe entry of migrants into India."
      ],
